President Obama has named 21 recipients of the Presidential Medal of Freedom, the nation's highest civilian honor. The award is given to individuals who have made significant contributions to the United States, world peace, or cultural endeavors. The recipients include basketball player Kareem Abdul-Jabbar, Native American advocate Elouise Cobell, comedian Ellen DeGeneres, actor Robert De Niro, physicist Richard Garwin, philanthropists Bill and Melinda Gates, architect Frank Gehry, mathematician Margaret H. Hamilton, actor Tom Hanks, computer scientist Grace Hopper, basketball player Michael Jordan, artist Maya Lin, producer Lorne Michaels, attorney Newt Minow, educator Eduardo Padr√≥n, actor Robert Redford, singer Diana Ross, broadcaster Vin Scully, musician Bruce Springsteen, and actress Cicely Tyson. The awards will be presented at the White House on November 22nd.